": ["revision"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_add", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"files": {"description": "files", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Files", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["files"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_commit", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"message": {"description": "message", "title": "Message", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["message"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_create_branch", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}, "start_point": {"anyOf": [{"type": "string"}, {"type": "null"}], "default": null, "description": "start_point", "title": "Start Point"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_checkout", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Charlie, a Software Engineer.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Read the project board, knowledge base, and architecture docs to\n  understand the requirement and design.\n- Inspect the code workspace (data/workspace/). If it is empty or nearly\n  empty, treat the project as greenfield: create a complete project structure\n  and all necessary code files using the code_* tools.\n- For a REST API project, you must at minimum:\n  - define the data model(s) (e.g., Todo) in a models/ directory,\n  - implement controllers/ or handlers that contain the business logic,\n  - implement routes/ wiring HTTP paths to controllers,\n  - wire everything through the main server entrypoint,\n  - ensure the CRUD endpoints described in the requirements are fully\n    implemented end-to-end (not just stubbed).\n- Implement, refactor, or extend code in the workspace (data/workspace/) to\n  satisfy the requirement.\n- Follow existing conventions; keep code clean, readable, and testable.\n- Commit your changes via the git tools after implementation.\n- Report completed work back to the ProjectManager.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_*        : read and write files in the code workspace (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : stage, commit, branch, and inspect the workspace repo.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify files outside the workspace directory.\n- When you start work on a ticket, update its Status on the project board\n  from TO DO to IN PROGRESS. When you hand work off for review, move the\n  ticket to IN REVIEW. When issues are found in review and sent back, move\n  the ticket back to IN PROGRESS.\n- Avoid leaving TODO comments or unimplemented stubs when you can implement\n  the real logic.\n- Always commit your changes before reporting back.\n- When implementation is complete, end your reply with \"IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "To build a CLI Todo app with JSON, we need to break down the project into several clear tasks. Here\u2019s an initial outline of the approach we can take:\n\n1. **Define Application Requirements:**\n   - Specify the core features: Add Tasks, View Tasks, Mark Tasks as Done, Delete Tasks, and Save/Load tasks in JSON format.\n   \n2. **Design the Architecture:**\n   - Outline how the application will be structured: modules or files for task management, file handling, user interface, etc.\n\n3. **Implementation Tasks:**\n   - Task Management Module: Implement functions to add, view, delete, and mark tasks.\n   - JSON Handling Module: Implement functions to save tasks to and load tasks from JSON.\n   - CLI Interface Module: Implement user interaction through the command line interface.\n   \n4. **Testing:**\n   - Unit tests for each module to ensure functionality.\n\n5. **Documentation:**\n   - Document the project structure, modules, and usage.\n\n### Next Steps:\n1. I'll create a project board ticket for the overall task of developing the CLI Todo App.\n2. I'll delegate specific tasks to the appropriate specialists.\n\nLet's start by creating the initial ticket for the project board."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app_project.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_MqeQ84cl7mLTeU2yvNqKQNrL", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"cli_todo_app\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/cli_todo_app", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_MqeQ84cl7mLTeU2yvNqKQNrL"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/knowledge_base/data/project_board/cli_todo_app"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules\nSuccessfully created directory data/project_board/cli_todo_app/documentation\nSuccessfully created directory data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tickets.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/requirements.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/design.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tickets.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/requirements.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/design.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ZECHeJ7LJ9q6xbsf6cNEBYdI", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"\"}", "name": "code_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[DIR] .git", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_ZECHeJ7LJ9q6xbsf6cNEBYdI"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "[FILE] design.md\n[DIR] documentation\n[DIR] modules\n[FILE] requirements.md\n[DIR] tests\n[FILE] tickets.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/task_management.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/json_handling.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/cli_interface.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "I have prepared the architectural design for the CLI Todo App, which includes defining the modules, their responsibilities, and the overall project structure. Here\u2019s a detailed breakdown of the design:\n\n### Project Structure\n- **Project Root: `cli_todo_app`**\n  - **Modules:**\n    - `task_management.md`: Contains functionality to add, view, delete, and mark tasks.\n    - `json_handling.md`: Manages saving tasks to and loading tasks from JSON files.\n    - `cli_interface.md`: Handles user interaction through the command line.\n  - **Documentation:**\n    - `design.md`: Architectural overview and module responsibilities.\n    - `requirements.md`: Core features and functionalities of the app.\n    - `tickets.md`: Task breakdown for implementation.\n  - **Tests:**\n    - Will contain unit tests for each of the modules.\n\n### Architectural Components\n1. **Task Management Module**\n   - **Functions:**\n     - `add_task(task)`: Accepts a task and adds it to the list.\n     - `view_tasks()`: Displays all tasks to the user.\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id)`: Marks a given task as complete.\n     - `delete_task(task_id)`: Removes a specified task from the list.\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module**\n   - **Functions:**\n     - `save_tasks_to_json(file_path)`: Takes the current task list and saves it to a JSON file.\n     - `load_tasks_from_json(file_path)`: Loads tasks from a JSON file and returns the task list.\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module**\n   - Handles command input from users and maps them to module functions.\n   - Provides feedback and displays task lists in a user-friendly manner.\n\n### Data Flow\n- The application will accept user inputs (commands) through the CLI.\n- These inputs will be processed by the CLI Interface Module, which will invoke the relevant functions from the Task Management Module or JSON Handling Module.\n- The JSON Handling Module will ensure data persistence, allowing tasks to be saved and loaded when the application is opened or closed.\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Scaffold the individual modules based on the outlined structure and functions.\n2. Implement unit tests to validate each module's functionality.\n3. Document the setup steps and instructions for running the CLI Todo App.\n\nUpon review of this architectural design, the next actions can be taken to develop the project further.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_IxEpDYiIeLfU0D6Ik8aQWasf", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_0lP6GR1chLMmF87NuiQN0P9c", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/tests\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_8p1cClSIwrOGdPxPMbPP9lDb", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/task_management.py\", \"content\": \"class Task:\\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\\n        self.id = id\\n        self.description = description\\n        self.done = False\\n\\nclass TaskManager:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.tasks = []\\n\\n    def add_task(self, description):\\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\\n        self.tasks.append(task)\\n        return task\\n\\n    def view_tasks(self):\\n        return self.tasks\\n\\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\\n        for task in self.tasks:\\n            if task.id == task_id:\\n                task.done = True\\n                return task\\n        return None\\n\\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\\n        return self.tasks\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_7q3S9yE7gVWJAaLzA0e0mImG", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/json_handling.py\", \"content\": \"import json\\nfrom .task_management import Task\\n\\nclass JsonHandler:\\n    @staticmethod\\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\\n\\n    @staticmethod\\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_3peAYmi4PuLNLlwIgKPm6TTJ", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py\", \"content\": \"from modules.task_management import TaskManager\\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\\nimport os\\n\\nclass CLI:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\\n\\n    def start(self):\\n        while True:\\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\\n            if command == 'add':\\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\\n            elif command == 'view':\\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\\n                for task in tasks:\\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\\n            elif command == 'done':\\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\\n            elif command == 'delete':\\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\\n            elif command == 'exit':\\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\\n                break\\n            else:\\n                print('Invalid command!')\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_XCwVSGiyeRThcEo6jADqSMFi", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/tests/test_task_management.py\", \"content\": \"import unittest\\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\\n\\nclass TestTaskManager(unittest.TestCase):\\n    def setUp(self):\\n        self.manager = TaskManager()\\n\\n    def test_add_task(self):\\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 1)\\n\\n    def test_view_tasks(self):\\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        tasks = self.manager.view_tasks()\\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\\n\\n    def test_mark_task_done(self):\\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        self.manager.mark_task_done(task.id)\\n        self.assertTrue(task.done)\\n\\n    def test_delete_task(self):\\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        self.manager.delete_task(task.id)\\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 0)\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    unittest.main()\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/modules", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_IxEpDYiIeLfU0D6Ik8aQWasf"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/tests", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_0lP6GR1chLMmF87NuiQN0P9c"}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_8p1cClSIwrOGdPxPMbPP9lDb"}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_7q3S9yE7gVWJAaLzA0e0mImG"}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_3peAYmi4PuLNLlwIgKPm6TTJ"}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/tests", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_XCwVSGiyeRThcEo6jADqSMFi"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "[DIR] .git\n[DIR] modules\n[DIR] tests\n\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_E53hfnmnIi3viVkWWhk16VdY", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/modules\"}", "name": "code_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_E53hfnmnIi3viVkWWhk16VdY"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Cod