sks to a JSON file\\n- Load tasks from a JSON file\\n\\n## Functions\\n1. `save_tasks(tasks: List[Task], file_path: str): void`\\n   - Saves the tasks to a JSON file at `file_path`.\\n2. `load_tasks(file_path: str) -> List[Task]`\\n   - Loads tasks from a JSON file at `file_path`.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_12kfPDKeAZeClx67VBaLmXTO", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/cli_interface.md\", \"content\": \"# CLI Interface Module\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n- Handle user input and output to the terminal\\n\\n## Functions\\n1. `display_menu(): void`\\n   - Displays the main menu options to the user.\\n2. `get_user_choice(): int`\\n   - Gets the user's choice from the menu.\\n3. `show_tasks(tasks: List[Task]): void`\\n   - Displays the list of tasks to the user.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/task_management.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_H4oKxLvlk26yKn8qYWIZOAQd"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/json_handling.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_1v31ha8HiWyzixc9N4ofkIsf"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/cli_interface.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_12kfPDKeAZeClx67VBaLmXTO"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "I have prepared the architectural design for the CLI Todo App, which includes defining the modules, their responsibilities, and the overall project structure. Here\u2019s a detailed breakdown of the design:\n\n### Project Structure\n- **Project Root: `cli_todo_app`**\n  - **Modules:**\n    - `task_management.md`: Contains functionality to add, view, delete, and mark tasks.\n    - `json_handling.md`: Manages saving tasks to and loading tasks from JSON files.\n    - `cli_interface.md`: Handles user interaction through the command line.\n  - **Documentation:**\n    - `design.md`: Architectural overview and module responsibilities.\n    - `requirements.md`: Core features and functionalities of the app.\n    - `tickets.md`: Task breakdown for implementation.\n  - **Tests:**\n    - Will contain unit tests for each of the modules.\n\n### Architectural Components\n1. **Task Management Module**\n   - **Functions:**\n     - `add_task(task)`: Accepts a task and adds it to the list.\n     - `view_tasks()`: Displays all tasks to the user.\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id)`: Marks a given task as complete.\n     - `delete_task(task_id)`: Removes a specified task from the list.\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module**\n   - **Functions:**\n     - `save_tasks_to_json(file_path)`: Takes the current task list and saves it to a JSON file.\n     - `load_tasks_from_json(file_path)`: Loads tasks from a JSON file and returns the task list.\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module**\n   - Handles command input from users and maps them to module functions.\n   - Provides feedback and displays task lists in a user-friendly manner.\n\n### Data Flow\n- The application will accept user inputs (commands) through the CLI.\n- These inputs will be processed by the CLI Interface Module, which will invoke the relevant functions from the Task Management Module or JSON Handling Module.\n- The JSON Handling Module will ensure data persistence, allowing tasks to be saved and loaded when the application is opened or closed.\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Scaffold the individual modules based on the outlined structure and functions.\n2. Implement unit tests to validate each module's functionality.\n3. Document the setup steps and instructions for running the CLI Todo App.\n\nUpon review of this architectural design, the next actions can be taken to develop the project further.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/modules\nSuccessfully created directory data/workspace/tests\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/modules\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/tests"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "[DIR] .git\n[DIR] modules\n[DIR] tests\n\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_XKkKH1ZxhbCEkVj9nhurQHk6", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.md\",\"content\":\"# Unit Tests for Task Management Module\\n\\n## Test Cases\\n1. **Test Add Task**\\n   - **Input**: Add a task with description \\\"Buy groceries\\\"\\n   - **Expected Output**: Task list contains the newly added task.\\n\\n2. **Test View Tasks**\\n   - **Expected Output**: Should return a list of all tasks including added tasks.\\n\\n3. **Test Mark Task Done**\\n   - **Input**: Mark the first task as done\\n   - **Expected Output**: The task status should be updated to completed.\\n\\n4. **Test Delete Task**\\n   - **Input**: Delete the first task\\n   - **Expected Output**: Task list should no longer contain the deleted task.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_XKkKH1ZxhbCEkVj9nhurQHk6"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": ""}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "data/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/task_management.md:\n# Task Management Module\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Add a task to the list\n- View all tasks\n- Mark a task as completed\n- Delete a task from the list\n\n## Functions\n1. `add_task(description: str): void`\n   - Adds a task with the provided description.\n2. `view_tasks(): List[str]`\n   - Returns a list of all tasks.\n3. `mark_task_done(task_id: int): void`\n   - Marks the task at `task_id` as completed.\n4. `delete_task(task_id: int): void`\n   - Deletes the task at `task_id`.\n\n---\ndata/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/json_handling.md:\n# JSON Handling Module\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Save tasks to a JSON file\n- Load tasks from a JSON file\n\n## Functions\n1. `save_tasks(tasks: List[Task], file_path: str): void`\n   - Saves the tasks to a JSON file at `file_path`.\n2. `load_tasks(file_path: str) -> List[Task]`\n   - Loads tasks from a JSON file at `file_path`.\n\n---\ndata/project_board/cli_todo_app/modules/cli_interface.md:\n# CLI Interface Module\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Handle user input and output to the terminal\n\n## Functions\n1. `display_menu(): void`\n   - Displays the main menu options to the user.\n2. `get_user_choice(): int`\n   - Gets the user's choice from the menu.\n3. `show_tasks(tasks: List[Task]): void`\n   - Displays the list of tasks to the user.\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_rvNikqmNlTZbdkEtn26S2Lac", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.md\", \"content\": \"# Unit Tests for JSON Handling Module\\n\\n## Test Cases\\n1. **Test Save Tasks**\\n   - **Input**: Save a list of tasks to a JSON file.\\n   - **Expected Output**: The file should exist and contain the exact task data.\\n\\n2. **Test Load Tasks**\\n   - **Input**: Load tasks from a valid JSON file.\\n   - **Expected Output**: The loaded tasks should match the original task list.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_3QmmkKFLmxss0C4yNIkKmLON", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_cli_interface.md\", \"content\": \"# Unit Tests for CLI Interface Module\\n\\n## Test Cases\\n1. **Test Display Menu**\\n   - **Expected Output**: Should display the menu options correctly to the user.\\n2. **Test Get User Choice**\\n   - **Expected Output**: Should return an integer corresponding with user input.\\n3. **Test Show Tasks**\\n   - **Input**: Show tasks with a sample task list.\\n   - **Expected Output**: Tasks should display correctly formatted and readable.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_rvNikqmNlTZbdkEtn26S2Lac"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_cli_interface.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_3QmmkKFLmxss0C4yNIkKmLON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The development of the CLI Todo App is progressing well, with the architectural design, modules, their responsibilities, and testing plans fully documented. Here\u2019s an overview of what has been accomplished so far:\n\n### Modules Overview\n1. **Task Management Module**\n   - Responsibilities include adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `add_task(description: str)`\n     - `view_tasks()`\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id: int)`\n     - `delete_task(task_id: int)`\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module**\n   - Manages the persistence of tasks through JSON files.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `save_tasks(tasks: List[Task], file_path: str)`\n     - `load_tasks(file_path: str) -> List[Task]`\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module**\n   - Handles user interaction through the command line.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `display_menu()`\n     - `get_user_choice()`\n     - `show_tasks(tasks: List[Task])`\n\n### Testing Overview\n- **Test Plan for Task Management Module**: Documented with unit tests for adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\n- **Test Plan for JSON Handling Module**: Includes tests for saving to and loading from JSON files, and handling invalid files.\n- **Test Plan for CLI Interface Module**: Outlines tests for menu display and user input handling.\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Begin implementation of the modules based on the outlined architecture.\n2. Write unit tests as part of the continuous integration process.\n3. Maintain clear documentation throughout the development for future reference.\n\nThis structured approach ensures that we are on track to deliver a well-functioning CLI Todo App.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/task_management.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/json_handling.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "data/workspace/modules/task_management.py:\nclass Task:\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\n        self.id = id\n        self.description = description\n        self.done = False\n\nclass TaskManager:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.tasks = []\n\n    def add_task(self, description):\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\n        self.tasks.append(task)\n        return task\n\n    def view_tasks(self):\n        return self.tasks\n\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\n        for task in self.tasks:\n            if task.id == task_id:\n                task.done = True\n                return task\n        return None\n\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\n        return self.tasks\n\n---\ndata/workspace/modules/json_handling.py:\nimport json\nfrom .task_management import Task\n\nclass JsonHandler:\n    @staticmethod\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\n\n---\ndata/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py:\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\nimport os\n\nclass CLI:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\n\n    def start(self):\n        while True:\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\n            if command == 'add':\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\n            elif command == 'view':\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\n                for task in tasks:\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\n            elif command == 'done':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\n            elif command == 'delete':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\n            elif command == 'exit':\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\n                break\n            else:\n                print('Invalid command!')\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "class Task:\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\n        self.id = id\n        self.description = description\n        self.done = False\n\nclass TaskManager:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.tasks = []\n\n    def add_task(self, description):\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\n        self.tasks.append(task)\n        return task\n\n    def view_tasks(self):\n        return self.tasks\n\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\n        for task in self.tasks:\n            if task.id == task_id:\n                task.done = True\n                return task\n        return None\n\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\n        return self.tasks\nimport json\nfrom .task_management import Task\n\nclass JsonHandler:\n    @staticmethod\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\nimport os\n\nclass CLI:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\n\n    def start(self):\n        while True:\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\n            if command == 'add':\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\n            elif command == 'view':\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\n                for task in tasks:\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\n            elif command == 'done':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\n            elif command == 'delete':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\n            elif command == 'exit':\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\n                break\n            else:\n                print('Invalid command!')"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_AGp9yENj7ukfpmlKQeqXTMqd", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.py\", \"content\": \"import unittest\\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\\n\\nclass TestTaskManager(unittest.TestCase):\\n    def setUp(self):\\n        self.manager = TaskManager()\\n\\n    def test_add_task(self):\\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test task')\\n        self.assertEqual(task.description, 'Test task')\\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.view_tasks()), 1)\\n\\n    def test_view_tasks(self):\\n        self.manager.add_task('Task 1')\\n        self.manager.add_task('Task 2')\\n        tasks = self.manager.view_tasks()\\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 2)\\n\\n    def test_mark_task_done(self):\\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Task to mark done')\\n        self.manager.mark_task_done(task.id)\\n        self.assertTrue(task.done)\\n\\n    def test_delete_task(self):\\n        task1 = self.manager.add_task('Task 1')\\n        self.manager.delete_task(task1.id)\\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.view_tasks()), 0)\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    unittest.main()\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_kxBgbMCwfDFkJEQQggRlATJ2", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.py\", \"content\": \"import unittest\\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\\nfrom modules.task_management import Task\\nimport os\\n\\nclass TestJsonHandler(unittest.TestCase):\\n    def setUp(self):\\n        self.tasks = [Task(1, 'Task 1'), Task(2, 'Task 2')]\\n        self.file_path = 'test_tasks.json'\\n\\n    def test_save_load_tasks(self):\\n        JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.tasks, self.file_path)\\n        loaded_tasks = JsonHandler.load_tasks_from_json(self.file_path)\\n        self.assertEqual(len(loaded_tasks), len(self.tasks))\\n        for i, task in enumerate(loaded_tasks):\\n            self.assertEqual(task.id, self.tasks[i].id)\\n            self.assertEqual(task.description, self.tasks[i].description)\\n\\n    def tearDown(self):\\n        if os.path.exists(self.file_path):\\n            os.remove(self.file_path)\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    unittest.main()\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_psO9OIQksU8j8aNnC2QJSPb4", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_cli_interface.py\", \"content\": \"import unittest\\nfrom modules.cli_interface import CLI\\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\\n\\nclass TestCLI(unittest.TestCase):\\n    @patch('builtins.input', side_effect=['add', 'Test Task', 'exit'])\\n    def test_add_task(self, mock_input):\\n        cli = CLI()\\n        cli.start()\\n        self.assertEqual(len(cli.task_manager.view_tasks()), 1)\\n        self.assertEqual(cli.task_manager.view_tasks()[0].description, 'Test Task')\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    unittest.main()\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_AGp9yENj7ukfpmlKQeqXTMqd"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_kxBgbMCwfDFkJEQQggRlATJ2"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_cli_interface.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_psO9OIQksU8j8aNnC2QJSPb4"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The implementation phase for the CLI Todo App has been completed successfully. Here\u2019s a summary of the modules that have been developed along with the corresponding tests:\n\n### Implemented Modules\n1. **Task Management Module (`task_management.py`)**\n   - **Classes:**\n     - `Task`: Represents a single task with an ID, description, and status.\n     - `TaskManager`: Manages a list of tasks with functions to add, view, mark, and delete tasks.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `add_task(description)`: Adds a new task.\n     - `view_tasks()`: Returns the current list of tasks.\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id)`: Marks a specific task as completed.\n     - `delete_task(task_id)`: Removes a task from the list.\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module (`json_handling.py`)**\n   - **Class:**\n     - `JsonHandler`: Handles saving and loading tasks in JSON format.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path)`: Saves the task list to a JSON file.\n     - `load_tasks_from_json(file_path)`: Loads tasks from a JSON file into task objects.\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module (`cli_interface.py`)**\n   - **Class:**\n     - `CLI`: Manages the command-line interface for user interaction.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `start()`: Starts the CLI loop, processing user commands to add, view, mark, delete tasks, and exit while saving tasks.\n\n### Testing Overview\n- **Test Plans for Each Module** have been documented and implemented in the following test files:\n  - `test_task_management.py`: Tests for the functionality of the Task Manager.\n  - `test_json_handling.py`: Tests for JSON handling, ensuring tasks are saved and loaded correctly.\n  - `test_cli_interface.py`: Tests user interactions through the CLI, validating command processing and task management operations.\n\n### Next Steps\n- Run the unit tests to ensure that all functionalities are working as expected.\n- Gather feedback and make necessary adjustments based on testing results.\n- Prepare for a potential deployment of the application to users.\n\nThe project is now fully set up and ready for the next phases of testing and refinement.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/tests/test_task_management.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/tests/test_json_handling.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/tests/test_cli_interface.py"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "data/workspace/tests/test_task_management.py:\nimport unittest\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\n\nclass TestTaskManager(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.manager = TaskManager()\n\n    def test_add_task(self):\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 1)\n\n    def test_view_tasks(self):\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        tasks = self.manager.view_tasks()\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\n\n    def test_mark_task_done(self):\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.manager.mark_task_done(task.id)\n        self.assertTrue(task.done)\n\n    def test_delete_task(self):\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.manager.delete_task(task.id)\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 0)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n\n---\ndata/workspace/tests/test_json_handling.py:\nimport unittest\nimport os\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler, Task\n\nclass TestJsonHandler(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.task = Task(1, 'Test Task')\n        self.file_path = 'test_tasks.json'\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        if os.path.exists(self.file_path):\n            os.remove(self.file_path)\n\n    def test_save_and_load_tasks(self):\n        JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json([self.task], self.file_path)\n        tasks = JsonHandler.load_tasks_from_json(self.file_path)\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\n        self.assertEqual(tasks[0].description, 'Test Task')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n\n---\ndata/workspace/tests/test_cli_interface.py:\nimport unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom modules.cli_interface import CLI\n\nclass TestCLI(unittest.TestCase):\n    @patch('builtins.input', side_effect=['add', 'Test Task', 'view', 'exit'])\n    @patch('modules.json_handling.JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json')\n    def test_cli_add_view_exit(self, mock_save, mock_input):\n        cli = CLI()\n        cli.start()\n        self.assertEqual(len(cli.task_manager.tasks), 1)\n        self.assertEqual(cli.task_manager.tasks[0].description, 'Test Task')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "import unittest\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\n\nclass TestTaskManager(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.manager = TaskManager()\n\n    def test_add_task(self):\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 1)\n\n    def test_view_tasks(self):\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        tasks = self.manager.view_tasks()\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\n\n    def test_mark_task_done(self):\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.manager.mark_task_done(task.id)\n        self.assertTrue(task.done)\n\n    def test_delete_task(self):\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\n        self.manager.delete_task(task.id)\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 0)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\nimport unittest\nimport os\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler, Task\n\nclass TestJsonHandler(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.task = Task(1, 'Test Task')\n        self.file_path = 'test_tasks.json'\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        if os.path.exists(self.file_path):\n            os.remove(self.file_path)\n\n    def test_save_and_load_tasks(self):\n        JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json([self.task], self.file_path)\n        tasks = JsonHandler.load_tasks_from_json(self.file_path)\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\n        self.assertEqual(tasks[0].description, 'Test Task')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\nimport unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom modules.cli_interface import CLI\n\nclass TestCLI(unittest.TestCase):\n    @patch('builtins.input', side_effect=['add', 'Test Task', 'view', 'exit'])\n    @patch('modules.json_handling.JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json')\n    def test_cli_add_view_exit(self, mock_save, mock_input):\n        cli = CLI()\n        cli.start()\n        self.assertEqual(len(cli.task_manager.tasks), 1)\n        self.assertEqual(cli.task_manager.tasks[0].description, 'Test Task')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DKIt8hOYGuRgtoO2Zk06gjMT1e8Z6", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_VPHskzFjsark4nmy016FrCgM", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_runner.py\",\"content\":\"import unittest\\nimport os\\n\\n# Discover and run all tests in the tests directory\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    test_dir = './tests/'\\n    test_suite = unittest.defaultTestLoader.discover(test_dir)\\n    runner = unittest.TextTestRunner()\\n    runner.run(test_suite)\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773731538, "model": "gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_6b1ef07cda", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 96, "prompt_tokens": 7598, "total_tokens": 7694, "completion_tokens_details": {"ac