verview\n1. **Task Management Module**\n   - Responsibilities include adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `add_task(description: str)`\n     - `view_tasks()`\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id: int)`\n     - `delete_task(task_id: int)`\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module**\n   - Manages the persistence of tasks through JSON files.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `save_tasks(tasks: List[Task], file_path: str)`\n     - `load_tasks(file_path: str) -> List[Task]`\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module**\n   - Handles user interaction through the command line.\n   - Key Functions:\n     - `display_menu()`\n     - `get_user_choice()`\n     - `show_tasks(tasks: List[Task])`\n\n### Testing Overview\n- **Test Plan for Task Management Module**: Documented with unit tests for adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\n- **Test Plan for JSON Handling Module**: Includes tests for saving to and loading from JSON files, and handling invalid files.\n- **Test Plan for CLI Interface Module**: Outlines tests for menu display and user input handling.\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Begin implementation of the modules based on the outlined architecture.\n2. Write unit tests as part of the continuous integration process.\n3. Maintain clear documentation throughout the development for future reference.\n\nThis structured approach ensures that we are on track to deliver a well-functioning CLI Todo App.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_eM2uy02R4IX0fE7pYbloig14", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/task_management.py\", \"content\": \"class Task:\\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\\n        self.id = id\\n        self.description = description\\n        self.done = False\\n\\nclass TaskManager:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.tasks = []\\n\\n    def add_task(self, description):\\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\\n        self.tasks.append(task)\\n        return task\\n\\n    def view_tasks(self):\\n        return self.tasks\\n\\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\\n        for task in self.tasks:\\n            if task.id == task_id:\\n                task.done = True\\n                return task\\n        return None\\n\\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\\n        return self.tasks\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_ABfhT1p7JjCSG8smoUxlTnEq", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/json_handling.py\", \"content\": \"import json\\nfrom .task_management import Task\\n\\nclass JsonHandler:\\n    @staticmethod\\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\\n\\n    @staticmethod\\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_PoJ0f2eLuf93THBh5RfcWg9F", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py\", \"content\": \"from modules.task_management import TaskManager\\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\\nimport os\\n\\nclass CLI:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\\n\\n    def start(self):\\n        while True:\\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\\n            if command == 'add':\\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\\n            elif command == 'view':\\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\\n                for task in tasks:\\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\\n            elif command == 'done':\\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\\n            elif command == 'delete':\\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\\n            elif command == 'exit':\\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\\n                break\\n            else:\\n                print('Invalid command!')\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/task_management.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_eM2uy02R4IX0fE7pYbloig14"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/json_handling.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_ABfhT1p7JjCSG8smoUxlTnEq"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_PoJ0f2eLuf93THBh5RfcWg9F"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "data/workspace/modules/task_management.py:\nclass Task:\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\n        self.id = id\n        self.description = description\n        self.done = False\n\nclass TaskManager:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.tasks = []\n\n    def add_task(self, description):\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\n        self.tasks.append(task)\n        return task\n\n    def view_tasks(self):\n        return self.tasks\n\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\n        for task in self.tasks:\n            if task.id == task_id:\n                task.done = True\n                return task\n        return None\n\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\n        return self.tasks\n\n---\ndata/workspace/modules/json_handling.py:\nimport json\nfrom .task_management import Task\n\nclass JsonHandler:\n    @staticmethod\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\n\n---\ndata/workspace/modules/cli_interface.py:\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\nimport os\n\nclass CLI:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\n\n    def start(self):\n        while True:\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\n            if command == 'add':\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\n            elif command == 'view':\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\n                for task in tasks:\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\n            elif command == 'done':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\n            elif command == 'delete':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\n            elif command == 'exit':\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\n                break\n            else:\n                print('Invalid command!')\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "class Task:\n    def __init__(self, id, description):\n        self.id = id\n        self.description = description\n        self.done = False\n\nclass TaskManager:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.tasks = []\n\n    def add_task(self, description):\n        task_id = len(self.tasks) + 1\n        task = Task(task_id, description)\n        self.tasks.append(task)\n        return task\n\n    def view_tasks(self):\n        return self.tasks\n\n    def mark_task_done(self, task_id):\n        for task in self.tasks:\n            if task.id == task_id:\n                task.done = True\n                return task\n        return None\n\n    def delete_task(self, task_id):\n        self.tasks = [task for task in self.tasks if task.id != task_id]\n        return self.tasks\nimport json\nfrom .task_management import Task\n\nclass JsonHandler:\n    @staticmethod\n    def save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'w') as json_file:\n            json.dump([task.__dict__ for task in tasks], json_file)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def load_tasks_from_json(file_path):\n        with open(file_path, 'r') as json_file:\n            task_list = json.load(json_file)\n            return [Task(**task) for task in task_list]\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\nfrom modules.json_handling import JsonHandler\nimport os\n\nclass CLI:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager()\n        self.file_path = 'tasks.json'\n\n    def start(self):\n        while True:\n            command = input('Enter a command (add/view/done/delete/exit): ')\n            if command == 'add':\n                description = input('Enter task description: ')\n                self.task_manager.add_task(description)\n            elif command == 'view':\n                tasks = self.task_manager.view_tasks()\n                for task in tasks:\n                    status = '\u2713' if task.done else '\u2717'\n                    print(f'Task {task.id}: {task.description} [{status}]')\n            elif command == 'done':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to mark as done: '))\n                self.task_manager.mark_task_done(task_id)\n            elif command == 'delete':\n                task_id = int(input('Enter task ID to delete: '))\n                self.task_manager.delete_task(task_id)\n            elif command == 'exit':\n                JsonHandler.save_tasks_to_json(self.task_manager.view_tasks(), self.file_path)\n                print('Tasks saved. Exiting.');\n                break\n            else:\n                print('Invalid command!')"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_task_management.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_json_handling.py\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app/tests/test_cli_interface.py"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The implementation phase for the CLI Todo App has been completed successfully. Here\u2019s a summary of the modules that have been developed along with the corresponding tests:\n\n### Implemented Modules\n1. **Task Management Module (`task_management.py`)**\n   - **Classes:**\n     - `Task`: Represents a single task with an ID, description, and status.\n     - `TaskManager`: Manages a list of tasks with functions to add, view, mark, and delete tasks.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `add_task(description)`: Adds a new task.\n     - `view_tasks()`: Returns the current list of tasks.\n     - `mark_task_done(task_id)`: Marks a specific task as completed.\n     - `delete_task(task_id)`: Removes a task from the list.\n\n2. **JSON Handling Module (`json_handling.py`)**\n   - **Class:**\n     - `JsonHandler`: Handles saving and loading tasks in JSON format.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `save_tasks_to_json(tasks, file_path)`: Saves the task list to a JSON file.\n     - `load_tasks_from_json(file_path)`: Loads tasks from a JSON file into task objects.\n\n3. **CLI Interface Module (`cli_interface.py`)**\n   - **Class:**\n     - `CLI`: Manages the command-line interface for user interaction.\n     \n   - **Key Functions:**\n     - `start()`: Starts the CLI loop, processing user commands to add, view, mark, delete tasks, and exit while saving tasks.\n\n### Testing Overview\n- **Test Plans for Each Module** have been documented and implemented in the following test files:\n  - `test_task_management.py`: Tests for the functionality of the Task Manager.\n  - `test_json_handling.py`: Tests for JSON handling, ensuring tasks are saved and loaded correctly.\n  - `test_cli_interface.py`: Tests user interactions through the CLI, validating command processing and task management operations.\n\n### Next Steps\n- Run the unit tests to ensure that all functionalities are working as expected.\n- Gather feedback and make necessary adjustments based on testing results.\n- Prepare for a potential deployment of the application to users.\n\nThe project is now fully set up and ready for the next phases of testing and refinement.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_TgbrINdJgA5pf8RmBdNPpMc0", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/tests/test_task_management.py\", \"content\": \"import unittest\\nfrom modules.task_management import TaskManager\\n\\nclass TestTaskManager(unittest.TestCase):\\n    def setUp(self):\\n        self.manager = TaskManager()\\n\\n    def test_add_task(self):\\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        self.assertEqual(len(self.manager.tasks), 1)\\n\\n    def test_view_tasks(self):\\n        self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n        tasks = self.manager.view_tasks()\\n        self.assertEqual(len(tasks), 1)\\n\\n    def test_mark_task_done(self):\\n        task = self.manager.add_task('Test Task')\\n      