s, including task management, JSON handling, and the command line interface.\n\n## Test Files\n1. **test_task_management.py**: Contains tests for the Task Management module.\n2. **test_json_handling.py**: Contains tests for the JSON Handling module.\n3. **test_cli_interface.py**: Contains tests for the CLI interface.\n4. **test_runner.py**: A script to run all the tests in this directory.\n\n## Running the Tests\nTo execute all tests, run the following command in your terminal:\n```bash\npython -m unittest discover -s tests\n```\nMake sure to have all necessary modules installed and set up before running the tests."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_testing.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_overview.md"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DKItlANIAv7aUn8JOKvuCWII9HiL1", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_NwZX5NNb211RYnb3pWsNvMNz", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_testing.md\", \"content\": \"# CLI Todo App Testing Documentation\\n\\n## Overview\\nThis document provides insights into the testing strategy of the CLI Todo application, detailing the purpose and structure of the tests implemented.\\n\\n## Testing Structure\\nThe tests are organized into separate modules, each targeting specific functionalities within the CLI Todo application.\\n\\n### Test Files\\n1. **test_task_management.py**: Tests the functionality related to task management, including adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\\n2. **test_json_handling.py**: Tests the saving and loading capabilities of tasks in JSON format.\\n3. **test_cli_interface.py**: Tests the command-line interface and user interaction flow.\\n4. **test_runner.py**: A simpler script to aggregate those tests and run them efficiently.\\n\\n## Running the Tests\\nFor running the tests, ensure all dependencies are installed, then execute:\\n```bash\\npython -m unittest discover -s tests\\n```\"}", "name": "docs_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_5MRHZDPDjNO9EVpjFDtOl85n", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_overview.md\", \"content\": \"# CLI Todo Application Overview\\n\\n## Purpose\\nThe CLI Todo application enables users to manage tasks via a command-line interface efficiently. This application allows adding, viewing, marking, deleting tasks, and maintaining task data in a JSON format.\\n\\n## Features\\n- **Add Task**: Create a new task with a description.\\n- **View Tasks**: List all current tasks with their statuses (completed or not).\\n- **Mark Task as Done**: Update a task's status to completed.\\n- **Delete Task**: Remove a task from the list.\\n- **Persistent Storage**: Save tasks to a JSON file and load them at the start of the application.\\n\\n## Architecture\\nThe application is divided into the following modules:\\n1. **Task Management Module**: Handles task operations.\\n2. **JSON Handling Module**: Manages data serialization/deserialization in JSON.\\n3. **CLI Interface Module**: Processes user input/output.\\n\\nOverall, the CLI Todo application aims to provide a simple yet effective way to keep track of personal tasks.\"}", "name": "docs_write_file"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773731577, "model": "gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_a1681c17ec", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 486, "prompt_tokens": 7229, "total_tokens": 7715, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6912}}}, "prompt_tokens": 7229, "completion_tokens": 486, "agent_id": "Architect_6fda33fc-6e9c-