n.\\\\n\\\\n### Test Files\\\\n1. **test_task_management.py**: Tests the functionality related to task management, including adding, viewing, marking, and deleting tasks.\\\\n2. **test_json_handling.py**: Tests the saving and loading capabilities of tasks in JSON format.\\\\n3. **test_cli_interface.py**: Tests the command-line interface and user interaction flow.\\\\n4. **test_runner.py**: A simpler script to aggregate those tests and run them efficiently.\\\\n\\\\n## Running the Tests\\\\nFor running the tests, ensure all dependencies are installed, then execute:\\\\n```bash\\\\npython -m unittest discover -s tests\\\\n```\\\"}\",\"name\":\"docs_write_file\"},{\"id\":\"call_5MRHZDPDjNO9EVpjFDtOl85n\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_overview.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"# CLI Todo Application Overview\\\\n\\\\n## Purpose\\\\nThe CLI Todo application enables users to manage tasks via a command-line interface efficiently. This application allows adding, viewing, marking, deleting tasks, and maintaining task data in a JSON format.\\\\n\\\\n## Features\\\\n- **Add Task**: Create a new task with a description.\\\\n- **View Tasks**: List all current tasks with their statuses (completed or not).\\\\n- **Mark Task as Done**: Update a task's status to completed.\\\\n- **Delete Task**: Remove a task from the list.\\\\n- **Persistent Storage**: Save tasks to a JSON file and load them at the start of the application.\\\\n\\\\n## Architecture\\\\nThe application is divided into the following modules:\\\\n1. **Task Management Module**: Handles task operations.\\\\n2. **JSON Handling Module**: Manages data serialization/deserialization in JSON.\\\\n3. **CLI Interface Module**: Processes user input/output.\\\\n\\\\nOverall, the CLI Todo application aims to provide a simple yet effective way to keep track of personal tasks.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"docs_write_file\"}],\"type\":\"ToolCallRequestEvent\"},{\"id\":\"d23d005f-9294-47b4-a918-bbed2aa78843\",\"s